About
FRAMELESS is redefining the experiential immersive art world. Situated in Marble Arch, we are the largest permanent multi-sensory experience in the UK. FRAMELESS features four galleries and showcases some of the world’s greatest works of art presented in ways never seen before. Where art breaks free.
Duration: 1-2 hours

  • summerdays83
    59 contributions
    If you want your kids to love and appreciate art? Bring them to this
    An experience for the whole family to enjoy. Went there on a Friday morning before the half term holidays with my 4, 8 and 10 year old, and it was a morning well spent. We got a discount as a result of running in the GOSH Race for the Kids a few weekends ago, and it was a rainy day so after checking the reviews decided to give this a go. A seamless experience from start to finish, from ordering the tickets to travelling to the venue. We’ve been to the Van Gogh immersive experience before in Malaysia, and recently the BBC Earth Experience at Earl’s Court, and the kids enjoyed both but I’d say this one topped them. There are 4 rooms with different themes, from one focused on abstract art, one on surrealism, one on colour in motion (impressionist era) and the last on the world around us. We spent 2.5 hours there and still my 10 year old complained about leaving - this from a kid who couldn’t wait to leave the Louvre after less than an hour. The combination of the music, the immersive artwork spanning the whole room - from floor to ceiling - and the use of panels and mirrors, you just sit down and take it all in and let the time flow. Even more of a bonus that there was a cafe and good gift shop attached, where my 8 year old was only too keen to purchase a book on an artist. I appreciate art more after going to Frameless, and I know my kids loved it too. Well worth it.
    Frameless
    Hi, thank you for your detailed review and recommendation. We are so pleased you and your whole family enjoyed the experience. We hope your children continue to be inspired by art.

Andy L
East Horsley, UK111 contributions
Such a brilliant hour and a half visit. Do go.
Nov 2024 • Couples
This exhibition was stunning. Very clever and very interesting. So good to see well known paintings brought to life with animations. There are 4 galleries to visit with different themes, all superb and using many different paintings in each room. We particularly loved the Colour in Motion gallery, which simulated the brush strokes and "created" the end image on the wall. So clever, and fascinating to watch. And it was amazing how the designers of these galleries married such appropriate music to each 20 minute show.
We would highly recommend anyone who loves art, and wants to see it in a different and fascinating way, to come and visit Frameless.
Review of: Frameless - Immersive Art Experience in London

david b
1 contribution
Surprised and delighted.
Nov 2024 • Couples
Far exceeded my expectations. Went into the World Around Us first. Amazing scale of the images all around. So much careful thought went into the sequencing and musical score. Next the Colour in Motion: great fun watching the seasonal effects and more importantly people's (especially young people's) reactions. Loved seeing children dancing together! Third movement of the Quartet for us was The Art of Abstraction. I thought this worked brilliantly as a spectator sitting in one of the very well-sited benches. Jazzy and magical and so imaginative! The final movement for us was Beyond Reality. At first this was a little disappointing for me, as I felt it was large, but it was less immersive. But conceptually, it was also exciting and pointed to future possibilities. So I left very well satisfied with my first experience of immersive art!
